/*******************************************************************
 * File:    gc/gcstate.doc
 * Purpose: describe state garbage collector
 * Author:  Karl Abrahamson
 *******************************************************************/

seen_states: A list of states.  Each state s in seen_states has each of its
	     boxes in marked_boxes, and, for each box b in marked_boxes,
	     the content of box b in state s has been marked.

marked_boxes: A set of boxes.  See seen_states.

External interface:
-------------------

mark_state_gc(s):  
		
		   For each box b in s, place b in marked_boxes if not already
			there
		   For each state t in the tree below s, mark t.
		   For each box b in marked_boxes, mark the content of b in s.
		   Add s to seen_states.

mark_box_gc(b): Mark the content of box b in each state s in seen_states.
		Place b in marked_boxes.


mark_box_range_gc(a,b,s): Mark the content of box x in each state s in 
			  seen_states, for each x in
			  {a,...,b} that is not in set s.  Return the
			  set s union {a,...,b}.


Internal:
-----------

mark_all_state_gc(s): 
		For each box b in state s, place b in marked_boxes and
		mark each state node in the tree below s.

mark_state_with_gc(s,mins,maxs,bs,minbs,maxbs):
		For each b in set bs, mark the content of b in state s.
		All boxes in s are known to lie between mins and maxs.
		All members of set bs are known to lie between minbs
		and maxbs.

mark_range_gc(minb, maxb, s, mins, maxs):
		Mark the contents of boxes minb to maxb in state s.
		All boxes in s are known to lie between mins and maxs.



